# Create the herdr-pings repo and extract the wake loop into it

## Step

Stand up public repo `joelhooks/herdr-pings` and move the wake loop there cleanly:

- `gh repo create joelhooks/herdr-pings --public` (description: "Turn-level wake events for agents in herdr panes — pi extension, wait CLI, herdr plugin").
- Move `herdr-turn-ping/` and `herdr-ping-wait/` from pi-tools (git mv + removal commit in pi-tools pointing at the new home).
- Root README: what it is, the spool contract gist, install steps (pi-extension symlink, CLI symlink) — copied forward from the existing READMEs, deduplicated. No operator-private context (public repo).
- Re-point the live symlinks: `~/.pi/agent/extensions/herdr-turn-ping` and `~/.local/bin/herdr-ping-wait` → the new checkout at `~/Code/joelhooks/herdr-pings`.
- Update the paths named in `~/.claude/skills/herdr-orchestration/SKILL.md` and the `herdr-wake-loop-standalone-repo` memory.
- Smoke after re-pointing: `HERDR_PANE_ID='wT:p9' pi -p "say hi"` appends to the spool; `herdr-ping-wait --timeout 3` behaves (exit 2, nothing new consumed unexpectedly).

Resolution: repo URL, the pi-tools removal commit, symlink receipts, and smoke output.

## Resolution (2026-07-12)

Done by pi worker `wF:p6`, verified by the steering session.

- Public repo live: https://github.com/joelhooks/herdr-pings (`39c074d`; MIT; README carries the spool contract + install one-liners, zero operator-private content — steering fixed one wrong upstream link post-review).
- pi-tools removal + pointer commit: `2041ace`, pushed. Both dirs gone from pi-tools.
- Live symlinks verified re-pointed: `~/.pi/agent/extensions/herdr-turn-ping` and `~/.local/bin/herdr-ping-wait` → `~/Code/joelhooks/herdr-pings/...`.
- herdr-orchestration skill and the standalone-repo memory updated to the new paths.
- Post-move smoke passed: one `turn_ended` appended by a fresh pi run; `herdr-ping-wait --timeout 3` exit 2 with nothing consumed.
